content.description:
Start kneebarred with hands free or on the underclings. Don't use the right ground boulder once you leave the kneebar. Cool surfboard.

 This might be Stool Softener. Unsure.
content.location: Farthest left boulder. You partially scramble over this boulder from the Dugout.

content.description:
Start on two juggy pockets. Very cool pockets through-out. Height-dependent. V2 if you can do the first two moves static. V3 or higher otherwise.

 Spotters recommended.
content.location: The first tall boulder past the Sperm Whale boulder

content.description:
Start matched on the sloper rail. Dyno or campus up the ledge and beach whale over. Fun and not fun at the same time. Two move wonder. Feels way different than other stuff around here. Watch out for the cactus.

 Spotters highly recommended.

Extension area to the Dugout, with fewer defined boulders and more short wall bouldering. The problems here are in dire need of cleaning but have excellent rock quality sparing two small chossy sections. Most of the same applies from the Dugout, except that there are more slopers here.
